Uses of Package
main.GuiWindows

  • Packages that use main.GuiWindows 
    Package Description
    main  
  • Classes in main.GuiWindows used by main 
    Class Description
    ChooseActionWindow
    This class implements the window for choosing a crew member action, which is shown when the user has chosen their crew member they would like to complete the action.
    ChooseCrewMemberWindow
    This class implements the window for choosing the crew member that the user would like to complete an action.
    ConsumeFoodWindow
    This class implements a window allowing the user to choose which food item they would like the chosen crew member to consume.
    CrewMemberStatusWindow
    This class implements the window for viewing the status of each crew member
    FoodItemWindow
    This class implements the window for allowing the user to view and purchase food items
    FoodOrMedicalWindow
    This class implements the window allowing the user to chose whether they would like the crew member to consume food or use a medical item from the ship's inventory.
    GameOverWindow
    This class implements the window to display the game over screen to the user
    IntroWindow
    This class implements the start up screen to introduce the player to the game
    InventoryWindow
    This class implements the window to display the crews current inventory to the player
    MainGameWindow
    This class implements the window for the main screen of the game which the player interacts with continuously in order to progress
    MarketWindow
    This class implements the window for visiting the market at an outpost
    MedicalItemWindow
    This class implements the window for allowing the user to view and purchase medical items
    NewPlanetWindow
    This class implements the window for choosing a second pilot then calls the method for traveling to a new planet
    OutpostWindow
    The class implements the window for when the user chooses to visit the nearest outpost where they can buy items or view their inventory
    SetupWindow
    This class implements the setup window so that the player may choose the number of days the adventure will last, their crew members, and name the ship and crew
    ShipStatusWindow
    This class implements the window for displaying the ships status to the player
    StatementWindow
    This class implements a window which is used multiple times throughout the game to display a statement, which is passed to it as an argument.
    UseMedicalWindow
    This class implements a window allowing the user to choose which medical item they would like the chosen crew member to use.
    WarningWindow
    This class implements the window for warning the user about various obstacles in the game such as a random event or when a crew members hunger or tiredness gets too high
